description: Test the electrical resistance across the timing potentiometer terminals while adjusting to verify if the potentiometer is functioning correctly or if its wiper is stuck internally., outcome="The system was unable to measure resistance or continuity for the 'Timing Potentiometer' because the component has no resistance parameter. The potentiometer wiper could be adjusted successfully, but its electrical characteristics cannot be evaluated further with available data.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=100.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('adjust_potentiometer', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('adjust_potentiometer', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> sensor-operated relay (control module),
description: Test the operation of the relay to check if it is switching as intended, or if it is experiencing abnormal periodic switching independent of the timing potentiometer setting., outcome="Inspection panel was opened successfully. The 'Control Relay' was visually inspected with no observable internal faults and is currently closed. Measured voltage at the relay is approximately 11.99 V (positive terminal) and 0.36 V (negative terminal) relative to ground.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=35.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient light sensor (control module),
description: Measure the voltage or signal output from the ambient light sensor during the periodic switching interval to determine if there are sudden changes in its output that may be causing the relay to open and close regardless of actual ambient light conditions., outcome='Voltage measured at the ambient light sensor is 0.119 V (positive terminal) and 0.0003 V (negative terminal) with respect to ground. No polarity inversion is detected in this measurement.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> lamp indicator (load module),
description: Test the small lamp indicator in the load module to see if it remains on or if it blinks in sync with the main lamp, indicating whether the issue is isolated to the relay/control circuit or also affects the downstream circuit., outcome='Both the Internal Indicator Lamp and the Main Load (lamp) are not lit. No observable internal faults were found in either bulb.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> diode (load module),
description: Test the diode in the load module to verify if it is functioning correctly, as a faulty or intermittently conducting diode could cause both lamps not to light even when the relay is closed and should be supplying voltage., outcome='The load protection diode was tested with a multimeter in diode-test mode. The measured forward voltage is 0.7\u202fV, matching the nominal value of 0.7\u202fV. The diode is functioning nominally.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_diode', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> output terminals of the control module (switched side),
description: Measure the voltage across the switchable output terminals of the control module (just before entering the load module) during the period when the lamp is supposed to be on and off, to verify if the control module is actually supplying power to the load when the relay is closed., outcome='Voltage at Control Output Cable (+) was 0.3592 V, and voltage at Control Output Cable (−) was 0.0003 V during the measurement. No polarity inversion was detected in cable connections based on the measurement steps described.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power Supply Output Cables,
description: Measure the voltage across the output terminals of the power supply module (at its output connectors, before entering the control module) to verify that a stable 12V is being provided to the control module under load., outcome='Voltage measurements show 11.99 V at PSU Output Cable (+) and approximately 0 V at PSU Output Cable (−), indicating a stable supply close to 12 V across the output terminals under load. No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module Internal Wiring,
description: Test the voltage inside the control module immediately after the relay output (at the point where the relay connects to the output wires), while relay is supposed to be closed. This will distinguish if the internal relay contact or the downstream wiring is open or resistive., outcome='Voltage at the control relay output terminal (positive) is 11.99 V, while the Control Output Cable (+) measures only 0.36 V, nearly identical to the negative side. This suggests there is an open or high resistance between the relay output terminal and the Control Output Cable (+). No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
